> Love breakfast-for-dinner? Try it Japanese-style - a gorgeous way to start or end the day! For our spin on this traditional dish, you'll whip up a savory miso-based soup that's packed with flavorful diced chicken thighs, sweet carrots, and a tasty trio of tender bok choy, cabbage, and scallions. On the side is a comforting bowl of fluffy white rice and a tangy cucumber salad for bright crunchy contrast.

In a #small pot{}, combine @White Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water (2¼ cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce.

While rice cooks, trim, peel, and halve @Carrots{6%oz} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Open package of @Diced Chicken Thighs{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, carrots, scallion whites, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in @Bok Choy and Napa Cabbage{4%oz}, @Miso Sauce Concentrate{2}, @Soy Sauce{2%tbsp}, and 2 cups water (4 cups for 4 servings). Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until veggies are tender, ~{4-6%minutes}. Taste and season with @salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch} if desired.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @Mini Cucumber{1} into rounds.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, scallion greens, @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, and @salt{1/2%tsp} (1 tsp sugar and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings).

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; divide between small serving bowls.

Ladle miso soup into separate #soup bowls{}. Serve soup and rice with cucumber salad on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.